President Biden and Vice President Harris spoke with Cherelle Griner, the wife of Brittney Griner who is currently detained in Russia. The President reassured Cherelle that he is working to secure Brittney's release, as well as the release of other U.S. nationals who are wrongfully detained or held hostage in Russia and around the world. He read Cherelle a draft of the letter he is sending to Brittney. The President offered his support to Cherelle and Brittney's family and promised to provide them with all possible assistance while his administration works to bring Brittney home. National Security Advisor Sullivan and Secretary of State Blinken have also spoken with Cherelle recently. The President has directed his national security team to remain in regular contact with Cherelle and other families of Americans held hostage or wrongfully detained abroad to keep them updated on rescue efforts.